	"contentText": "Week 3\n  \n  \n  \n    Overview\n\n\n\n\nFinancial intermediaries (banks/credit unions, investment banks, investment companies), security issuance process (private firms staying private or going public, public firms), mechanics of trading (brokers and dealers, trading costs, buying on margin, selling securities short), regulation of securities markets (government vs self-regulation, Sarbanes-Oxley Act, insider trading)\n\n\n\n\n \nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nhow different types of financial intermediaries allocate capital\nmutual fund fee structure\nhow firms raise capital in private offerings vs public markets\nthe mechanics of trading securities\ninvestor protection in the US\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading:\nLecture 2: lecture 2.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 2.pdf\n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \nAssignments and Quizzes\nA1\n \nAdditional Resources\nChapters 3 and 4\n \nClass Notes\nSep 2 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/IdTaBBrOJXrbpctzXxkkLL_cC4iW6GPdBVTiWpHAyk28oRdcDxkJ4u0J70m2aDho.NdRmXxJToXcGFWO8 \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: 6^e#^QHZ\n \n \nSep 4 class recording:\nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/nPy9TFj_cQ2gQpnO1v8T47n_92XPN94Zt_9oQDAd2qqXtI5B72dvh1Iu1mEwaqti.ZFcAlGUm3gobauwY\n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: ^H0Sn?9^\nClass notes:Fnce 3030 Sep 4.pdf\n    \n\nDownload Fnce 3030 Sep 4.pdf\n  \n  \n\n",
